{"lemma":"جُنَّةٌ","slug":"جُنَّةٌ","root":"ج.ن.ن","root_slug":"ج-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ن-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جُنَّة","root":"جنن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6381"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"garden"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paradise, heaven, the Paradise, the Heaven, Elysium"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جُنَّ (junna)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"madness, craziness, possession, mania"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a jinn, demon, genie","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jinn, demons, genies","tags":["Classical","plural","plural-only"],"examples":[{"text":"مِنَ ٱلْجِنَّةِ وَٱلنَّاسِ","english":"from among the jinn/demons and Men."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thing which veils, conceals, hides, covers, or protects"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weapon or armor, a thing used to protect oneself, anything protective or defensive"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"piece of cloth which a woman wears covering the face and the two sides of the bosom, a type of hijab or veil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic, the sense of a paradise being borrowed from Classical Syriac ܓܰܢܬܳܐ (gannəṯā). Compare Hebrew גַּן (gan), Aramaic גִּנָּא (ginnā), Ugaritic 𐎂𐎐 (gn). Synchronically, related to جَنّ (jann, “covering, protecting”)"},"ipa":["/d͡ʒan.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6381","headword_ar":"جُنَّةٌ","root":"jn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing by which a person is veiled, concealed, hidden, covered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protected: an arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armour, with which one protects himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything protective:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coats of mail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any defensive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protective, arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junanN","text_ar":"جُنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of cloth which a woman wears, covering the fore and kind parts of her head, but not the middle of it, and covering the face, and the two sides of the bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or, accord. to the M,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ornaments"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuliY~","text_ar":"حُلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobaY","text_ar":"جَنْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having two eyeholes, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroquE","text_ar":"بُرْقُع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AC%D9%86%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"جنة الأرواح","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_22","lexicon_en":"Al-Munāwī, al-Tawqīf ʿalā Muhimmāt al-Taʿārīf (d. 1622 CE)","lexicon_ar":"التوقيف على مهمات التعاريف للمناوي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=36484#8007f4","body_html":"<span>جنة الأرواح: تنويرها بحقائق العلم في حضرة الشهود الأقدس.</span><br>"}]}}